          "title": "Scene 5",
          "order": 4,
          "content": "<p>&quot;Vivian,&quot; he said. Just her name. Like a prayer. Like a question. Like he was asking permission for something he&#39;d already taken.</p><p>He pulled back and pushed in again. Long, deep strokes that made her feel every inch of him. She tried to stay in control — tried to set the pace, control the angle, keep her eyes closed and stay in her head. He wouldn&#39;t let her. His hand caught her wrist, pinned it above her head against the pillow. His other hand gripped her hip hard enough to bruise, holding her still while he fucked her deeper.</p><p>&quot;Look at me,&quot; he said again.</p><p>She did. And it destroyed her. His eyes were open and she could see everything in them — the control, the hunger, the desperation he was trying to hide. He was inside her and she could feel him losing his grip, and that knowledge — that she was the one cracking him open, that she was the one making this man come undone — was more intoxicating than the sex itself.</p><p>He fucked her harder. The bed frame hit the wall. She was making sounds she couldn&#39;t stop — not performing, not faking, just *responding* — and her second orgasm was building from somewhere deeper than the first. Somewhere she didn&#39;t know she had. He shifted his angle and hit something inside her that made her cry out, and his thumb found her clit again, circling in time with his thrusts.</p><p>&quot;Don&#39;t,&quot; she said. She didn&#39;t know what she was asking him not to do. Don&#39;t make her come. Don&#39;t make her feel this. Don&#39;t make her want him. Don&#39;t ruin her.</p><p>He didn&#39;t stop. His thumb pressed harder, his cock hitting that spot inside her with every thrust, and she came again — clenching around him in rhythmic pulses, her nails digging into his back hard enough to draw blood, a sound coming out of her throat that she&#39;d never heard before. Something between a scream and a sob. Something that felt like surrender.</p><p>He followed three strokes later. She felt him pulse inside her — thick and hot even through the condom — felt his body go rigid, felt the sound he made against her neck. Not controlled. Not managed. Just *human*. Raw and broken and real. His hips stuttered and he buried himself deep and for three seconds the mask was gone and he was just a man who&#39;d wanted her, who&#39;d needed her, who&#39;d let her see it.</p><p>Then it was over.</p><p>He pulled out carefully. She felt the loss of him immediately — the empty ache where he&#39;d been, the wetness between her legs, the marks on her hips and throat that would take days to fade. He rolled onto his back. Stared at the ceiling. His chest was rising and falling. Sweat on his skin. He looked, for the first time since she&#39;d met him, like someone who&#39;d just been fucked instead of someone who&#39;d just fucked her.</p><p>Neither of them spoke.</p>",
