        {
          "id": "sc-01-07",
          "title": "Scene 7",
          "order": 6,
          "content": "<p>&quot;The truth,&quot; he said. &quot;Just once.&quot;</p><p>She didn&#39;t give it to him. Not yet. But she didn&#39;t leave either.</p><p>She lay in that bed, in that room, next to a man who was either the monster she&#39;d been sent to destroy or something worse — something that knew her name, her mother&#39;s name, the exact weight of her — and she stared at the ceiling and felt the ground shift under everything she&#39;d built her mission on.</p><p>The Atlantic kept crashing. The roses kept breathing. And somewhere in the lining of her clutch, a dead earpiece heard nothing at all.</p>",
