          "title": "Scene 4",
          "order": 3,
          "content": "<p>His mouth was at her ear.</p><p>&quot;You want control?&quot; he said. &quot;Take it.&quot;</p><p>She pushed against his chest. He didn&#39;t move. She was strong — six years of combat training, Krav Maga, Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu — and he was just sitting there, immovable, waiting for her to realize she couldn&#39;t move him unless he let her.</p><p>She hated that.</p><p>She hated more that it turned her on.</p><p>She stopped pushing. Went still. Looked up at him.</p><p>His grey eyes were steady. Patient. Waiting.</p><p>&quot;Let me up,&quot; she said.</p><p>&quot;No.&quot;</p><p>&quot;Let me *up*.&quot;</p><p>&quot;Make me.&quot;</p><p>She twisted. Tried to slip out from under him. He caught both her wrists in one hand and pinned them above her head. His other hand slid up her thigh. Under the shirt she was wearing — his shirt. His fingers found the hem. Traced the edge of her underwear.</p><p>She stopped breathing.</p><p>&quot;You&#39;re fighting,&quot; he said against her neck. &quot;Why are you fighting?&quot;</p><p>&quot;Because I don&#39;t lose.&quot;</p><p>His fingers slipped under the silk. Traced her slowly. She was soaking.</p><p>&quot;You&#39;re not losing,&quot; he said. &quot;You&#39;re choosing to surrender. There&#39;s a difference.&quot;</p><p>&quot;There&#39;s no difference.&quot;</p><p>His fingers circled her clit and her hips bucked off the desk.</p><p>&quot;There&#39;s every difference,&quot; he said. &quot;Losing is when you have no choice. This — &quot; He pushed one finger inside her. &quot;This is you choosing to let me touch you. You can stop me anytime.&quot;</p><p>She couldn&#39;t. She knew she couldn&#39;t. Not because he was stronger — though he was — but because her body had already decided. Before her brain caught up. Before the mission. Before any of it.</p><p>His thumb pressed her clit while his finger moved inside her — slow, deliberate, relentless. She was gripping the edge of the desk with her free hand. Making sounds she didn&#39;t recognize.</p><p>&quot;Look at me,&quot; he said.</p><p>She opened her eyes. He was watching her face. Reading every micro-expression. Every time her breath hitched. Every time her eyes fluttered closed and she forced them open.</p><p>She was losing. Again. The orgasm was building despite everything. Despite the fact that this was supposed to be dominance. Despite the fact that she&#39;d started this.</p><p>He added a second finger. Stretching her. His thumb circled her clit and pleasure coiled so tight she couldn&#39;t breathe.</p><p>&quot;Come for me,&quot; he said.</p><p>She did. It ripped through her — clenching around his fingers, her thighs shaking, a sound tearing out of her throat. He worked her through it. Drawing it out. Slower and slower until the last shudder passed.</p><p>He pulled his hand away. Brought his fingers to his mouth. Tasted her.</p><p>Then he stood. Lifted her off the desk. Set her on her feet.</p><p>&quot;My turn,&quot; he said.</p><p>He unbuckled his belt. Pushed his trousers down. His cock was hard — thick, the head flushed dark. He rolled a condom on.</p><p>He turned her around. Bent her over the desk. His hand on the small of her back, pressing her down. The head of his cock pressed against her and she gripped the far edge of the desk and he pushed in.</p>",
          "wordCount": 518
