          "id": "sc-03-05",
          "title": "Scene 5",
          "order": 4,
          "content": "<p>The stretch of him made her gasp. He was thick. Too thick. He paused when he was fully inside her and she could feel him throbbing and the ache of it was unbearable.</p><p>&quot;Vivian,&quot; he said. Just her name.</p><p>He pulled back and pushed in again. Hard. The desk scraped against the floor. Papers fell. She was making sounds she couldn&#39;t stop and his hand found her clit again, circling in time with his thrusts.</p><p>&quot;You tried to dominate me,&quot; he said against her ear. His breath ragged. &quot;How&#39;s that working out?&quot;</p><p>She couldn&#39;t answer. Her second orgasm was building from somewhere deeper. Somewhere she didn&#39;t have a name for.</p><p>He fucked her harder. She gripped the desk. Her nails scratching the wood. The pleasure was too much. Too big. She was going to break apart.</p><p>&quot;Don&#39;t,&quot; she said. She didn&#39;t know what she was asking him not to do.</p><p>He didn&#39;t stop.</p><p>She came again — clenching around him in rhythmic pulses, a sound like a sob tearing out of her throat. He followed two strokes later, pulsing inside her, his forehead pressed against her shoulder blade, a sound like a groan torn from somewhere deep.</p><p>Then it was over.</p><p>He pulled out carefully. She stayed bent over the desk, breathing hard, her legs shaking. She could feel his wetness leaking down her thigh.</p><p>She straightened slowly. Turned around. Her legs were unsteady. Her hair was a mess. Her face was burning.</p><p>He was watching her. His expression unreadable.</p><p>&quot;That wasn&#39;t control,&quot; she said.</p><p>&quot;No,&quot; he agreed. &quot;It wasn&#39;t.&quot;</p><p>&quot;I was supposed to dominate you.&quot;</p><p>&quot;You tried.&quot;</p><p>&quot;I failed.&quot;</p><p>&quot;You surrendered.&quot; He tilted his head. &quot;There&#39;s a difference.&quot;</p><p>She hated that he was right. She hated more that she wanted to do it again.</p><p>She picked up his shirt from where it had fallen. Pulled it on. Fixed her hair. Reset her face.</p><p>&quot;I&#39;m going to shower,&quot; she said. &quot;And then I&#39;m going to go through every file on those hard drives. And if I find so much as one discrepancy — &quot;</p><p>&quot;You&#39;ll burn me. I know.&quot;</p><p>She walked to the door. Stopped. Looked back.</p><p>He was still standing by the desk. Still half-undressed. Still watching her.</p><p>&quot;The cameras in the study,&quot; she said. &quot;You have them recording right now.&quot;</p><p>&quot;Yes.&quot;</p><p>&quot;So you have footage of this.&quot;</p><p>&quot;Yes.&quot;</p><p>She should be furious. Should be threatening. Should be doing something other than feeling the ghost of him still pulsing inside her.</p><p>&quot;Delete it,&quot; she said.</p><p>&quot;No.&quot;</p><p>&quot;Delete it or I swear to God — &quot;</p><p>&quot;No,&quot; he said again. &quot;This is mine. I&#39;m keeping it.&quot;</p><p>Her stomach dropped. Not in fear. In something worse.</p><p>She left the study. Closed the door behind her. Walked down the hallway to the master suite. Locked the bathroom door. Turned on the shower. Stood under the water and let it run over her.</p><p>She&#39;d just fucked the man she was sent to destroy. On his desk. While his cameras recorded everything. And the worst part — the part that made her want to punch the tile wall — was that she&#39;d wanted to. Had started it. Had *chosen* it.</p>",
